### Test Notification Endpoints
### Make sure to replace YOUR_TOKEN with actual Bearer token from login

### 1. Login as Admin
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@123.com",
  "password": "Admin@123"
}

### 2. Get My Notifications (Use token from login response)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/notifications/my?status=PENDING&limit=5
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN

### 3. Get All My Notifications
GET http://localhost:3000/api/notifications/my?limit=10
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN

### 4. Get My Sent Notifications
GET http://localhost:3000/api/notifications/my?status=SENT&limit=5
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN

### 5. Get Notification Settings
GET http://localhost:3000/api/notifications/settings
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN

### 6. Create Another Test Notification for Yourself
POST http://localhost:3000/api/notifications
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "JOB_CREATED",
  "title": "Another Test Notification",
  "message": "This is another test to verify /my endpoint works",
  "method": "SMS",
  "recipient": "0771234567",
  "recipientType": "ADMIN",
  "recipientUserId": "d8ba1bc3-7417-4c1f-9fc2-6dbf3d1d92cb",
  "priority": "HIGH"
}

### 7. Get All Notifications (Admin view)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/notifications?limit=10
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN
